id: pm-bzx3
title: Investigate validate/health telemetry classification (71-74% failure rate)
description: "KPI report 2026-05-16 shows validate=73.68% and health=71.71% finish_failure_rate over 7d. Both commands intentionally exit non-zero when findings exist; the classifier counts these as command_failed. Add a soft-failure resolution (e.g. validation_findings, health_findings) so KPIs distinguish bugs from intentional non-zero exits."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[4]: classification,observability,pm-cli,telemetry
created_at: "2026-05-16T21:54:18.262Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-16T23:45:07.292Z"
author: maintainer-agent
acceptance_criteria: validate/health soft-failures (run completed; findings present) reported as a distinct resolution code; KPI report shows realistic error rates for diagnostics family.
parent: pm-rnpb
resolution: Implemented dedicated health_findings and validation_findings telemetry classifications plus report filters for soft diagnostic findings.
expected_result: Health/validate strict-exit findings are distinguishable from runtime bugs and excluded from failure-rate KPI columns.
actual_result: "Focused telemetry regression, live telemetry query, dogfood, and full release gate passed."
